=== 19世紀 ===
西元1882年，時任[[美國司法部長|司法部長]]的正式意见认为，由於该条款是针对议员的任期而言的，而即便议员辞职，该任期仍然存在，因此自議員辞职依然不能使總統任命其擔任有於其任內提升待遇之聯邦职务。<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=47 Op. Att'y Gen. No. 17|url=https://dojmt.gov/wp-content/uploads/1998/01/47-017.pdf|format=PDF|language=en|accessdate=2021-04-18|archive-date=2020-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201016181520/https://dojmt.gov/wp-content/uploads/1998/01/47-017.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

因此，即使前爱荷华州州长{{Internal link helper/en|塞繆爾·柯克伍德|Samuel J. Kirkwood}}辞去了任期到1883年3月才屆滿的参议员席位，他仍然没有资格被任命为美国关税专员。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Recent Patent and Trade Mark Decisions|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/scientificamerican08081896-134a|date=1896-08-08|journal=Scientific American|issue=6|doi=10.1038/scientificamerican08081896-134a|volume=75|pages=134–135|issn=0036-8733|access-date=2021-04-17|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417021137/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/recent-patent-and-trade-mark-decisi-1896-08/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1896年，财政部主计长事后认定，前参议员馬修·蘭森擔任驻墨西哥大使的任命无效<ref>{{Cite news|title=KNOX SEEMS BARRED FROM THE CABINET; Because He Was a Senator When the Salary of the Secretary of State Was Increased. CONSTITUTION SO PROVIDES Inhibition Runs During His Full Term, So Resignation Now Would Not Qualify Him -- Has Been Disregarded in Some Minor Cases.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1909/02/10/archives/knox-seems-barred-from-the-cabinet-because-he-was-a-senator-when.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1909-02-10|accessdate=2021-04-18|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Special to The New York|last=Times|archive-date=2018-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613210729/https://www.nytimes.com/1909/02/10/archives/knox-seems-barred-from-the-cabinet-because-he-was-a-senator-when.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，因为在蘭森的參議員任期内，该职务的待遇曾有增加；这一迟来的发现使得蘭森不能领取工资。<ref name=":1">See 2 Decisions of the Comptroller of the Treasury 135 (1896).</ref>

=== 20世紀 ===
西元1909年，總統當選人[[威廉·霍华德·塔夫脱|塔夫脱]]宣布將提名參議员菲蘭德·C·諾克斯擔任国务卿<ref>{{Cite web|title=43 Cong. Rec. (Bound) - House of Representatives: February 23, 1909|url=https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/GPO-CRECB-1909-pt3-v43/pdf/GPO-CRECB-1909-pt3-v43-17-2.pdf|author=House|date=1909-02-24|format=PDF|pages=2950-2985|language=en|accessdate=2021-04-18|archive-date=2021-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210418115056/https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/GPO-CRECB-1909-pt3-v43/pdf/GPO-CRECB-1909-pt3-v43-17-2.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。宣布后不久，该条款出现的问题让相关人员大吃一驚：諾克斯的參議員任期要到西元1911年才结束，而在该任期内，国会曾通過增加國務卿薪酬的法案。 對此，国会议员讨论了是否應恢复所有美国内阁成员的工资，在眾议院司法委员会的建议下，參議院通过了一项法案，只把国务卿的工资降到諾克斯參議員任期开始前的水平，认为这样就能解决这个问题。但[[美国众议院|美国众议院]]的反对声更多，同样的措施未能获得所需的三分之二票数，而这一操作通常只适用于没有争议的任命<ref name=":6">{{Cite news|url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1909/02/16/101867245.pdf|title=Way Clear For Knox to Enter Cabinet|language=en|format=PDF|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2021-04-17|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090413/https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1909/02/16/101867245.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>，在采用不同的程序规则后，该法案以173-115通过，[[西奥多·罗斯福|罗斯福]]总统随后签署了该法案<ref name=":6" />。 3月4日<ref>{{Cite news|title=KNOX RELIEF BILL PASSES IN SENATE; No Debate on Measure Reducing Emoluments of Secretary of State to Old Figure. TAFT OFFICIALLY SILENT John Sharp Williams Declares Repeal of Salary Advance Does Not Remove Constitutional Bar.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1909/02/12/archives/knox-relief-bill-passes-in-senate-no-debate-on-measure-reducing.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1909-02-12|accessdate=2021-04-18|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Special to The New York|last=Times|archive-date=2021-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210418115108/https://www.nytimes.com/1909/02/12/archives/knox-relief-bill-passes-in-senate-no-debate-on-measure-reducing.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，第一次薩克斯比法案生效，国务卿的工资（但不包括其他内阁成员的工资）从1.2万美元恢复到8000美元。<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/945179295|publisher=Nabu Press|date=2010|location=[Place of publication not identified]|isbn=1-175-39244-8|oclc=945179295|first=Horace|last=Greeley|title=Tribune almanac and political register.|access-date=2021-04-17|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090429/https://www.worldcat.org/title/tribune-almanac-and-political-register/oclc/945179295|dead-url=no}}</ref>3月5日，参议院確認了塔夫脱提名的所有内阁人员，<ref>{{Cite news|title=SENATE CONFIRMS TAFT'S CABINET; Tillman Attacks Meyer and Bailey Asks About Nagel's Standard Oil Retainer. LOEB WILL BE COLLECTOR Nominated for New York Post -- Collector Fowler Stirred Up Labor Against Taft's Candidacy.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1909/03/06/archives/senate-confirms-tafts-cabinet-tillman-attacks-meyer-and-bailey-asks.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1909-03-06|accessdate=2021-04-17|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Special to The New York|last=Times|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090414/https://www.nytimes.com/1909/03/06/archives/senate-confirms-tafts-cabinet-tillman-attacks-meyer-and-bailey-asks.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>3月6日，诺克斯上任。<ref>{{Cite news|title=CABINET OFFICERS BEGIN THEIR WORK; All Except Two of Taft's Aids Sworn in and Roosevelt Men Displaced. MacVEAGH TO LACK MONEY May Be Compelled to Borrow Before the New Tariff Law Goes Goes Into Effect.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1909/03/07/archives/cabinet-officers-begin-their-work-all-except-two-of-tafts-aids.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1909-03-07|accessdate=2021-04-17|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Special to The New York|last=Times|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090429/https://www.nytimes.com/1909/03/07/archives/cabinet-officers-begin-their-work-all-except-two-of-tafts-aids.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1922年，当参议员威廉·S·肯楊获准接受[[沃伦·盖玛利尔·哈定|沃倫·哈定]]總統提名担任聯邦第八巡迴法院的巡迴法官时<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Emoluments Clause|last=O'Connor|first=John|publisher=Steptoe & Johnson LLP|isbn=|url=https://www.steptoe.com/images/content/2/2/v1/2239/3658.PDF|access-date=2021-04-18|archive-date=2019-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402024120/https://www.steptoe.com/images/content/2/2/v1/2239/3658.PDF|dead-url=no}}</ref>，「無資格條款」的適用得到了进一步的界定。 時任司法部长哈里·M·多爾蒂所給出的结论是，該事件並無違法，因为该职位薪酬的增加发生在肯楊获提名时的參議員任期之前。 （多爾蒂的意见后来在柯林頓政府提名[[比尔·理查森|比爾·李察遜]]担任駐联合国大使时再度被提起。）<ref>{{Cite web|title=Application of the Ineligibility Clause|url=https://www.justice.gov/file/19881/download|author=CHRISTOPHER SCHROEDER|date=1996-12-31|format=PDF|accessdate=2021-04-18|archive-date=2021-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320175316/https://www.justice.gov/file/19881/download|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/12664760|publisher=West Pub. Co|date=1986|location=St. Paul, Minn.|isbn=0-314-93436-7|oclc=12664760|first=Ronald D.|last=Rotunda|first2=J. Nelson|last2=Young|title=Treatise on constitutional law : substance and procedure|access-date=2021-04-10|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417021136/https://www.worldcat.org/title/treatise-on-constitutional-law-substance-and-procedure/oclc/12664760|dead-url=no}}</ref>

尼克森政府在第一年就透過手段迴避了 「无资格条款」──他任命众议员[[唐纳德·拉姆斯菲尔德|唐納德·倫斯斐]]为经济办公室主任。虽然在唐納德作為議員的任职期间，该办公室的工资已经提高到42500美元<ref name=":9">{{Cite news|title=1969 Rise in Cabinet Pay Could Prove Bar to Saxbe|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1973/11/02/archives/1969-rise-in-cabinet-pay-could-prove-bar-to-saxbe.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1973-11-02|accessdate=2021-04-18|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Walter Rugaber Special to The New York|last=Times|archive-date=2021-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420054754/https://www.nytimes.com/1973/11/02/archives/1969-rise-in-cabinet-pay-could-prove-bar-to-saxbe.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，依照憲法，他並沒有就任該職務的權利。但唐納德并未因此而沒有獲得任命──唐納德是以同样的42,500美元的薪資兼任总统助理，这个職位不在该条款所限制的范围内。<ref name=":9" />

1973年10月20日，埃利奧特·理查森（Elliot Lee Richardson）辞去了其司法部長的職務，尼克森于11月1日提名了薩克斯比作為新任的司法部長。尽管時值[[水门事件|水门事件]]，但尼克森仍然認為参议院会通過其任命案。<ref>{{Cite book|title=Congress and the Nation IV Law and Law Enforcement|publisher=CQ Press|year=1977|page=563}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Senate, 75 to 10, Votes to Confirm Saxbe as Attorney General|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1973/12/18/archives/senate-75-to-10-votes-to-confirm-saxbe-as-attorney-general.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1973-12-18|accessdate=2021-04-18|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Lesley Oelsner Special to The New York|last=Times|archive-date=2021-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210418115108/https://www.nytimes.com/1973/12/18/archives/senate-75-to-10-votes-to-confirm-saxbe-as-attorney-general.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

与诺克斯事件一样，在宣布提名后，该条款的复杂性让薩克斯比和尼克森政府都感到意外。 1973年11月初，尼克松要求将司法部長的薪酬降低至1969年以前的水平，以作为对该问题的补救措施。 参议院司法委员会就如何正确解释 「无资格条款 」举行了几天的听证会。<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/77798045|publisher=Oxford University Press|date=2006|location=Oxford|isbn=978-0-19-534561-2|oclc=77798045|first=Sanford|last=Levinson|title=Our undemocratic constitution : where the constitution goes wrong (and how we the people can correct it)|access-date=2021-04-17|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090416/https://www.worldcat.org/title/our-undemocratic-constitution-where-the-constitution-goes-wrong-and-how-we-the-people-can-correct-it/oclc/77798045|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=S.2673 - 93rd Congress (1973-1974): A bill to insure that the compensation and other emoluments attached to the Office of Attorney General are those which were in effect on January 1, 1969.|url=https://www.congress.gov/bill/93rd-congress/senate-bill/2673|accessdate=2021-04-17|date=1973-11-28|last=McGee|first=Gale W.|work=www.congress.gov|archive-date=2017-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170917201604/https://www.congress.gov/bill/93rd-congress/senate-bill/2673|dead-url=no}}</ref>

宪法学教授们对該补救措施是否符合宪法提出了相互矛盾的意见，参议院随后根据代理司法部长羅伯特·博克的建议采取行动，颁布了[https://www.congress.gov/bill/93rd-congress/house-bill/11710 H.R.11710（Pub.L.93-178）] {{Wayback|url=https://www.congress.gov/bill/93rd-congress/house-bill/11710 |date=20210419084555 }}，将司法部长的薪酬降至1969年以前的水平，並認為如此就能解决无资格问题<ref name=":10">{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/61724346|date=2005|location=Washington, DC|isbn=1-59698-001-X|oclc=61724346|last=Heritage Foundation|title=The Heritage guide to the Constitution.|access-date=2021-04-17|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090416/https://www.worldcat.org/title/heritage-guide-to-the-constitution/oclc/61724346|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此舉受到参议院司法委员会的严厉批评。<ref name=":7">{{Cite book|chapter=Congress and Government|title=Congress and the Nation, 1973-1976, Vol. IV: The 93rd and 94th Congresses|url=http://sk.sagepub.com/cqpress/congress-and-the-nation-iv/n11.xml|publisher=CQ Press|date=1977|location=2300 N Street, NW,  Suite 800,  Washington  DC  20037  United States|isbn=978-1-60871-381-3|pages=746–842|doi=10.4135/9781483302676.n11|access-date=2021-04-17|archive-date=2018-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180602012225/http://sk.sagepub.com/cqpress/congress-and-the-nation-iv/n11.xml|dead-url=no}}</ref>

由於憲法問題並未佔主導地位，該法案在眾議院不像其於參議院那樣引起廣泛爭議，但該法案還面臨其他程序障礙<ref name=":7" />。12月10日，尼克松正式提出了薩克斯比的提名案<ref name=":7" />，司法委員會於12月13日批准了薩克斯比的任命案，參議院於12月17日以75-10票通過了該任命案，但十名民主黨參議員對於其合憲性表示關切<ref>{{Cite web|title=44 - Hillary Clinton's Fix|url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2008/11/hillary-clintons-fix.html|accessdate=2021-04-17|work=voices.washingtonpost.com|archive-date=2020-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031015532/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2008/11/hillary-clintons-fix.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。薩克斯比直到1974年1月4日才辭職。因為該條款明確禁止同時服務於國會及聯邦政府，這延遲了他作為內閣成員的時程表<ref name=":10" />。薩克斯比後來寫道，儘管他需要失去額外薪水（作為參議員，他每年可賺42,500美元） ，他仍然願意擔任聯邦職務。在他上任幾個月後，最高法院裁定該程序違憲，他需要償還已經獲得的工資。<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/43694399|publisher=Kent State University Press|date=2000|location=Kent, Ohio|isbn=0-87338-668-X|oclc=43694399|first=William B.|last=Saxbe|title=I've seen the elephant : an autobiography|access-date=2021-04-17|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090449/https://www.worldcat.org/title/ive-seen-the-elephant-an-autobiography/oclc/43694399|dead-url=no}}</ref>

隨後, [[吉米·卡特|吉米·卡特]]在任命[[埃德蒙·马斯基|埃德蒙·馬斯基]]為其國務卿時，成為了第一個使用此方法來進行聯邦職務任命的民主黨籍總統。 [[赛勒斯·万斯|賽勒斯·范錫]]於1980年4月28日辭職。卡特於隔日提名了馬斯基，而隨後參議院以94–27通過其任命案。<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=The Carter Presidency|title=Congress and the Nation, 1977-1980, Vol. V: The 95th and 96th Congresses|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.4135/9781483302683.n15|publisher=CQ Press|location=2300 N Street, NW,  Suite 800,  Washington  DC  20037  United States|isbn=978-0-87187-216-6|access-date=2021-04-17|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417090418/https://polyfill.io/v3/polyfill.min.js|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|chapter=Foreign Policy|title=Congress and the Nation, 1977-1980, Vol. V: The 95th and 96th Congresses|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.4135/9781483302683.n2|publisher=CQ Press|location=2300 N Street, NW,  Suite 800,  Washington  DC  20037  United States|isbn=978-0-87187-216-6}}</ref>

最高法院大法官[[劉易斯·鮑威爾|路易斯·鮑威爾]]於1987年退休後，[[罗纳德·里根|羅納德·雷根]]總統考慮提名[[奧林·哈奇|奧爾林·哈奇]]參議員以填補其席位。<ref name=":8">{{Cite news|title=BORK PICKED FOR HIGH COURT; REAGAN CITES HIS 'RESTRAINT'; CONFIRMATION FIGHT LOOMS|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/07/02/us/bork-picked-for-high-court-reagan-cites-his-restraint-confirmation-fight-looms.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1987-07-02|accessdate=2021-04-17|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Gerald M.|last=Boyd|first2=Special To the New York|last2=Times|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319190801/https://www.nytimes.com/1987/07/02/us/bork-picked-for-high-court-reagan-cites-his-restraint-confirmation-fight-looms.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=INSIDE FIGHT SEEN OVER COURT CHOICE|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/06/28/us/inside-fight-seen-over-court-choice.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1987-06-28|accessdate=2021-04-17|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Irvin|last=Molotsky|first2=Special To the New York|last2=Times|archive-date=2018-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826171006/https://www.nytimes.com/1987/06/28/us/inside-fight-seen-over-court-choice.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>但是在他任職議員期間，國會已經對大法官之待遇有所提升。儘管不清楚「無資格條款」問題該任命案中的作用力，1987年7月，哈奇被提名。<ref name=":8" />兩個月後，助理司法部長[[奧林·哈奇|奧林·哈奇]]在書面意見中拒絕了薩克斯比修復方案，認為該解決方案無法解決不合格條款問題（後來提名被參議院否決，該席位最終由[[安東尼·肯尼迪|安東尼·肯尼迪]]擔任。）<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Volokh Conspiracy - Hillary Clinton and the Emoluments Clause:|url=http://volokh.com/posts/1227548910.shtml|accessdate=2021-04-17|work=volokh.com|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126102155/http://volokh.com/posts/1227548910.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===21世紀===
